Why the trait exists on DockerManager directly (not via a wrapper struct): DockerManager already has the right lifecycle surface, constructor patterns are harness-specific anyway (each impl has its own connect/bootstrap), and a wrapper would just add an Arc layer with no payload. When the c2w harness lands it gets its own struct (C2wHarness) with its own state; they don't need to share a parent.

Method identifier choice: the trait takes agent_id consistently; the Docker impl maps agent_id -> 'xpressclaw-{agent_id}' container name internally, matching what the reconciler already does via format!() at call sites today. This lets future harnesses use whatever naming they want.

Dual accessor on AppState (both docker() and harness()) is temporary scaffolding. The harness() accessor is backed by the same DockerManager; there's no new connection. Subsequent commits migrate callers, and the final cleanup commit removes the docker() accessor + docker field when nothing references them.
